question: why? the ratio on mod rod 1 returns a total net loss of mana. (meaning, it costs mana and/or time to  heal that damage, plus the raw mana it costs to summon is greater than that which it returns).<br>
<br>
i see NO reason to use mod rod 1 in a group, unless:<br>
a) clerics and/or other valuable supportive casters needed mana<br>
b) you were grouped with an offensive caster which greatly outclassed you to the point where even after the crappy ratio was considered it was still more efficient to feed (i.e. 51 mage grouped with 60 wizzie)<br>
<br>
i see no reason why before trods &quot;good mages&quot; should be making mod rod 1's in a group...<br>
<br>
